data.meta_description: See a map of Woodburn, VA's population by race. Woodburn is 47.3% White, 6.1% Black, 21.7% Asian, 17.7% Hispanic, 1.0% Native American/Other, and 6.1% Multiracial.
data.text:
A map of Woodburn's Population by Race

Woodburn, Virginia had a population of 8,797 in 2020. It was 47.3% White, 6.1% Black, 21.7% Asian, 17.7% Hispanic, 1.0% Native American/Other, and 6.1% Multiracial. This map presents the population of Woodburn, with one dot drawn for each person counted in the 2020 Census, color-coded by race.

Of the 672 places in Virginia, Woodburn is the 140th most populous. This ranking is based on the Census definition of a place, which includes incorporated places like cities, towns, and villages, as well as unincorporated census-designated places (CDPs).

Woodburn 's White Population

4,164 residents of Woodburn identify as White, or 47.3%. This makes the White share of the population of Woodburn slightly less than the White share of the population of Virginia (58.6% White). Of the 672 places in Virginia, Woodburn is ranked #537 in terms of White residents as a share of the population.

Woodburn is more White than neighboring Merrifield (40.8% White) , and Annandale (29.3% White) . Woodburn is less White than neighboring Mantua (59.1% White) , Wakefield (63.8% White) , and Long Branch (56.6% White) .

Woodburn 's Black Population

540 residents of Woodburn identify as Black, or 6.1%. This makes the Black share of the population of Woodburn less than the Black share of the population of Virginia (18.3% Black). Of the 672 places in Virginia, Woodburn is ranked #381 in terms of Black residents as a share of the population.

Woodburn is more Black than neighboring Mantua (3.7% Black) , Wakefield (3.2% Black) , and Long Branch (3.1% Black) . Woodburn is less Black than neighboring Merrifield (6.5% Black) , and Annandale (9% Black) .

Woodburn 's Asian Population

1,906 residents of Woodburn identify as Asian, or 21.7%. This makes the Asian share of the population of Woodburn larger than the Asian share of the population of Virginia (7.1% Asian). Of the 672 places in Virginia, Woodburn is ranked #41 in terms of Asian residents as a share of the population.

Woodburn is more Asian than neighboring Mantua (21% Asian) , and Wakefield (18.6% Asian) . Woodburn is less Asian than neighboring Merrifield (31.2% Asian) , Annandale (24.5% Asian) , and Long Branch (25.7% Asian) .

Woodburn 's Hispanic Population

1,559 residents of Woodburn identify as Hispanic, or 17.7%. This makes the Hispanic share of the population of Woodburn slightly larger than the Hispanic share of the population of Virginia (10.5% Hispanic). Of the 672 places in Virginia, Woodburn is ranked #72 in terms of Hispanic residents as a share of the population.

Woodburn is more Hispanic than neighboring Merrifield (15.1% Hispanic) , Mantua (9.4% Hispanic) , Wakefield (8% Hispanic) , and Long Branch (9.7% Hispanic) . Woodburn is less Hispanic than neighboring Annandale (32.9% Hispanic) .

Woodburn 's Native American/Other Population

88 residents of Woodburn identify as American Indian/Alaska Native/Native Hawaiian/Pacific Islander/Other, or 1.0%. This makes the Native American/Other share of the population of Woodburn roughly similar to the Native American/Other share of the population of Virginia (0.8% Native American/Other). Of the 672 places in Virginia, Woodburn is ranked #127 in terms of Native American/Other residents as a share of the population.

Woodburn is more Native American/Other than neighboring Merrifield (0.7% Native American/Other) , Mantua (0.7% Native American/Other) , Wakefield (0.9% Native American/Other) , Annandale (0.6% Native American/Other) , and Long Branch (0.5% Native American/Other) .

Woodburn 's Multiracial Population

540 residents of Woodburn identify as Multiracial, or 6.1%. This makes the Multiracial share of the population of Woodburn roughly similar to the Multiracial share of the population of Virginia (4.7% Multiracial). Of the 672 places in Virginia, Woodburn is ranked #81 in terms of Multiracial residents as a share of the population.

Woodburn is more Multiracial than neighboring Merrifield (5.8% Multiracial) , Mantua (6% Multiracial) , Wakefield (5.5% Multiracial) , Annandale (3.7% Multiracial) , and Long Branch (4.5% Multiracial) .
